Content: My bike is a carburetor bike, and when it is -0*C, the cylinder doesn't get any gas. When it's warm outside the bike works totally normal. I can kick the kick start 50 times and the spark plug is still dry. carburetor should be clean tho since it starts well when it is stored in a warm place.
